<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1908-09-01T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1908-09-01T00:00:00-05:00" n="499" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d499">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 6292/130.</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Japanese Ambassador</gloss>
                                to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Japanese Embassy</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Buena Vista
                                        Spring, Pa.</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1908-09-01"><hi rend="italic">September 1,
                                    1908</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p>I am informed that imperial decree to postpone exposition will be dated
                            September 1, but published in Official Gazette of 2d to-morrow. This is
                            on line agreed upon Sunday. I also telegraphed to the President.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Takahira.</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>